#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.229"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.229:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.229:0.2"
msgid "18. Samuddavagga"
msgstr "18. The Ocean"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.229:0.3"
msgid "229. Dutiyasamuddasutta"
msgstr "229. The Ocean (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.158"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.229:1.1"
msgid "“‘Samuddo, samuddo’ti, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano bhāsati."
msgstr "“Mendicants, an uneducated ordinary person speaks of the ocean."

msgctxt "sn35.229:1.2"
msgid "Neso, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye samuddo."
msgstr "But that’s not the ocean in the training of the noble one."

msgctxt "sn35.229:1.3"
msgid "Mahā eso, bhikkhave, udakarāsi mahāudakaṇṇavo."
msgstr "That’s just a large body of water, a large sea of water."

msgctxt "sn35.229:1.4"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā "
"kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, "
"pleasant, sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn35.229:1.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye samuddo."
msgstr "This is called the ocean in the training of the noble one."

#. VAR: kulagaṇṭhikajātā → guḷāguṇṭhikajātā (bj) | kulaguṇḍikajātā (s1-3, km) | guṇaguṇikajātā (pts1) | kulāguṇḍikajātā (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.229:1.6"
msgid ""
"Etthāyaṃ sadevako loko samārako sabrahmako sassamaṇabrāhmaṇī pajā "
"sadevamanussā yebhuyyena samunnā tantākulakajātā kulagaṇṭhikajātā "
"muñjapabbajabhūtā, apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ saṃsāraṃ nātivattati … pe …."
msgstr ""
"And it’s here that this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this "
"population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—is for the most "
"part sunk. It’s become tangled like string, knotted like a ball of thread, "
"and matted like rushes and reeds, and it doesn’t escape the places of loss, "
"the bad places, the underworld, transmigration."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.229:2.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe … santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā "
"dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches … thoughts known by the mind "
"that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn35.229:2.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye samuddo."
msgstr "This is called the ocean in the training of the noble one."

msgctxt "sn35.229:2.3"
msgid ""
"Etthāyaṃ sadevako loko samārako sabrahmako sassamaṇabrāhmaṇī pajā "
"sadevamanussā yebhuyyena samunnā tantākulakajātā kulagaṇṭhikajātā "
"muñjapabbajabhūtā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ saṃsāraṃ nātivattatīti."
msgstr ""
"And it’s here that this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this "
"population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—is for the most "
"part sunk. It’s become tangled like string, knotted like a ball of thread, "
"and matted like rushes and reeds, and it doesn’t escape the places of loss, "
"the bad places, the underworld, transmigration."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.229:3.1"
msgid "Yassa rāgo ca doso ca,"
msgstr "Those who have discarded"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.229:3.2"
msgid "Avijjā ca virājitā;"
msgstr "greed, hate, and ignorance"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.229:3.3"
msgid "So imaṃ samuddaṃ sagāhaṃ sarakkhasaṃ,"
msgstr "have crossed the ocean so hard to cross,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.229:3.4"
msgid "Saūmibhayaṃ duttaraṃ accatari."
msgstr "with its sharks and monsters, its waves and dangers."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.229:4.1"
msgid "Saṅgātigo maccujaho nirupadhi,"
msgstr "They’ve got over clinging, given up death, and have no attachments."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.229:4.2"
msgid "Pahāsi dukkhaṃ apunabbhavāya;"
msgstr "They’ve given up suffering, so there are no more future lives."

#. <br>
#. VAR: na puneti → na pamāṇameti (bj, pts1) | na pamānameti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.229:4.3"
msgid "Atthaṅgato so na puneti,"
msgstr "They’ve come to an end, and cannot be measured;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.229:4.4"
msgid "Amohayī maccurājanti brūmī”ti."
msgstr "and they’ve confounded the King of Death, I say.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.229:4.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
